                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong red)</seg>The hand is very similar, or possibly even identical, to that of Ms. VatLib Aeth. 263 (Book of Isaiah, Ascension of Isaiah, Book of Daniel, s. LanVat 465, in which Ṣäga Mättä [sic (Ṣäga Mäṭaʿ?)] is indicated as possible scribe). On the dating of Aeth. 263, s. UhlPal.<date>Pre-1350 (?)</date>
